item.title: Analysis of the performance of U-Net neural networks for the segmentation of living cells
item.description: The automated analysis of microscopy images is a challenge in the context of single-cell tracking and quantification.

item.title: One Transformer Can Understand Both 2D & 3D Molecular Data
item.description: To achieve this goal, in this work, we develop a novel Transformer-based Molecular model called Transformer-M, which can take molecular data of 2D or 3D formats as input and generate meaningful semantic representations.

item.title: Real-Time Monitoring of User Stress, Heart Rate and Heart Rate Variability on Mobile Devices

item.title: Generative Models and Learning Algorithms for Core-Periphery Structured Graphs
item.description: In this paper, we focus on learning the core scores of a graph from its node attributes and connectivity structure.

item.title: Concise and interpretable multi-label rule sets
item.description: Multi-label classification is becoming increasingly ubiquitous, but not much attention has been paid to interpretability.

item.title: Diffusion Models for Graphs Benefit From Discrete State Spaces
item.description: Denoising diffusion probabilistic models and score matching models have proven to be very powerful for generative tasks.

item.title: Log-Linear-Time Gaussian Processes Using Binary Tree Kernels
item.description: We present a new kernel that allows for Gaussian process regression in $O((n+m)\log(n+m))$ time.

item.title: Centroid Distance Keypoint Detector for Colored Point Clouds
item.description: Results demonstrate that our proposed CED keypoint detector requires minimal computational time while attaining high repeatability.

item.title: When to Make Exceptions: Exploring Language Models as Accounts of Human Moral Judgment
item.description: Using a state-of-the-art large language model (LLM) as a basis, we propose a novel moral chain of thought (MORALCOT) prompting strategy that combines the strengths of LLMs with theories of moral reasoning developed in cognitive science to predict human moral judgments.

item.title: HYPRO: A Hybridly Normalized Probabilistic Model for Long-Horizon Prediction of Event Sequences
item.description: In this paper, we tackle the important yet under-investigated problem of making long-horizon prediction of event sequences.

item.title: MEDFAIR: Benchmarking Fairness for Medical Imaging
item.description: In this work, we introduce MEDFAIR, a framework to benchmark the fairness of machine learning models for medical imaging.

item.title: Dense Prediction Transformer for Scale Estimation in Monocular Visual Odometry
item.description: Monocular visual odometry consists of the estimation of the position of an agent through images of a single camera, and it is applied in autonomous vehicles, medical robots, and augmented reality.

item.title: Complementary consistency semi-supervised learning for 3D left atrial image segmentation
item.description: A complementary consistency training is formed by the inter-model perturbation between the primary model and the auxiliary models.

item.title: VICRegL: Self-Supervised Learning of Local Visual Features
item.description: Most recent self-supervised methods for learning image representations focus on either producing a global feature with invariance properties, or producing a set of local features.

item.title: On Background Bias in Deep Metric Learning
item.description: Deep Metric Learning trains a neural network to map input images to a lower-dimensional embedding space such that similar images are closer together than dissimilar images.

item.title: Robust Target Training for Multi-Source Domain Adaptation
item.description: Given any existing fully-trained one-step MSDA model, BORT$^2$ turns it to a labeling function to generate pseudo-labels for the target data and trains a target model using pseudo-labeled target data only.

item.title: COARSE3D: Class-Prototypes for Contrastive Learning in Weakly-Supervised 3D Point Cloud Segmentation
item.description: Annotation of large-scale 3D data is notoriously cumbersome and costly.

item.title: Rethinking Lipschitz Neural Networks for Certified L-infinity Robustness
item.description: Designing neural networks with bounded Lipschitz constant is a promising way to obtain certifiably robust classifiers against adversarial examples.

item.title: APAUNet: Axis Projection Attention UNet for Small Target in 3D Medical Segmentation
item.description: In 3D medical image segmentation, small targets segmentation is crucial for diagnosis but still faces challenges.

item.title: Cooperative Self-Training for Multi-Target Adaptive Semantic Segmentation
item.description: In this work we address multi-target domain adaptation (MTDA) in semantic segmentation, which consists in adapting a single model from an annotated source dataset to multiple unannotated target datasets that differ in their underlying data distributions.

item.title: Positive Pair Distillation Considered Harmful: Continual Meta Metric Learning for Lifelong Object Re-Identification
item.description: Lifelong object re-identification incrementally learns from a stream of re-identification tasks.

item.title: MBW: Multi-view Bootstrapping in the Wild
item.description: Our Multi-view Bootstrapping in the Wild (MBW) approach demonstrates impressive results on standard human datasets, as well as tigers, cheetahs, fish, colobus monkeys, chimpanzees, and flamingos from videos captured casually in a zoo.

item.title: FreDSNet: Joint Monocular Depth and Semantic Segmentation with Fast Fourier Convolutions
item.description: Our experiments show that FreDSNet has similar performance as specific state of the art methods for semantic segmentation and depth estimation.

item.title: How deep convolutional neural networks lose spatial information with training
item.description: Here, we (i) show empirically for various architectures that stability to image diffeomorphisms is achieved by spatial pooling in the first half of the net, and by channel pooling in the second half, (ii) introduce a scale-detection task for a simple model of data where pooling is learned during training, which captures all empirical observations above and (iii) compute in this model how stability to diffeomorphisms and noise scale with depth.

item.title: Monte Carlo Tree Search based Variable Selection for High Dimensional Bayesian Optimization
item.description: Bayesian optimization (BO) is a class of popular methods for expensive black-box optimization, and has been widely applied to many scenarios.

item.title: Explanation-by-Example Based on Item Response Theory
item.description: Intelligent systems that use Machine Learning classification algorithms are increasingly common in everyday society.

item.title: Learning the Spectrogram Temporal Resolution for Audio Classification
item.description: Starting from a high-temporal-resolution spectrogram such as one-millisecond hop size, we show that DiffRes can improve classification accuracy with the same computational complexity.

item.title: Rhythmic Gesticulator: Rhythm-Aware Co-Speech Gesture Synthesis with Hierarchical Neural Embeddings
item.description: We present a novel co-speech gesture synthesis method that achieves convincing results both on the rhythm and semantics.

item.title: Knowledge Unlearning for Mitigating Privacy Risks in Language Models

item.title: Learning to Collocate Visual-Linguistic Neural Modules for Image Captioning
item.description: This is because the language is only partially observable, for which we need to dynamically collocate the modules during the process of image captioning.

item.title: Mintaka: A Complex, Natural, and Multilingual Dataset for End-to-End Question Answering
item.description: We introduce Mintaka, a complex, natural, and multilingual dataset designed for experimenting with end-to-end question-answering models.

item.title: Improving Label-Deficient Keyword Spotting Using Self-Supervised Pretraining
item.description: In this paper, we investigate the use of self-supervised pretraining for the smaller KWS models in a label-deficient scenario.

item.title: Fill in Fabrics: Body-Aware Self-Supervised Inpainting for Image-Based Virtual Try-On
item.description: Previous virtual try-on methods usually focus on aligning a clothing item with a person, limiting their ability to exploit the complex pose, shape and skin color of the person, as well as the overall structure of the clothing, which is vital to photo-realistic virtual try-on.

item.title: Generating Synthetic Data with The Nearest Neighbors Algorithm
item.description: The $k$ nearest neighbor algorithm ($k$NN) is one of the most popular nonparametric methods used for various purposes, such as treatment effect estimation, missing value imputation, classification, and clustering.

item.title: The current state of single-cell proteomics data analysis
item.description: Sound data analysis is essential to retrieve meaningful biological information from single-cell proteomics experiments.

item.title: Attention Distillation: self-supervised vision transformer students need more guidance
item.description: In experiments on ImageNet-Subset and ImageNet-1K, we show that our method AttnDistill outperforms existing self-supervised knowledge distillation (SSKD) methods and achieves state-of-the-art k-NN accuracy compared with self-supervised learning (SSL) methods learning from scratch (with the ViT-S model).

item.title: Under the Cover Infant Pose Estimation using Multimodal Data
item.description: To address this, we present a novel dataset, Simultaneously-collected multimodal Mannequin Lying pose (SMaL) dataset, for under the cover infant pose estimation.

item.title: New Paradigms for Exploiting Parallel Experiments in Bayesian Optimization
item.description: However, a key limitation of BO is that it is an inherently sequential algorithm (one experiment is proposed per round) and thus cannot directly exploit high-throughput (parallel) experiments.

item.title: Uncertainty-Driven Active Vision for Implicit Scene Reconstruction
item.description: We evaluate our proposed approach on the ABC dataset and the in the wild CO3D dataset, and show that: (1) we are able to obtain high quality state-of-the-art occupancy reconstructions; (2) our perspective conditioned uncertainty definition is effective to drive improvements in next best view selection and outperforms strong baseline approaches; and (3) we can further improve shape understanding by performing a gradient-based search on the view selection candidates.

item.title: The Effectiveness of Masked Language Modeling and Adapters for Factual Knowledge Injection
item.description: This paper studies the problem of injecting factual knowledge into large pre-trained language models.

item.title: Learning Equivariant Segmentation with Instance-Unique Querying
item.description: Prevalent state-of-the-art instance segmentation methods fall into a query-based scheme, in which instance masks are derived by querying the image feature using a set of instance-aware embeddings.

item.title: SpeechCLIP: Integrating Speech with Pre-Trained Vision and Language Model
item.description: Data-driven speech processing models usually perform well with a large amount of text supervision, but collecting transcribed speech data is costly.

item.title: BVI-VFI: A Video Quality Database for Video Frame Interpolation
item.description: In order to narrow this research gap, we have developed a new video quality database named BVI-VFI, which contains 540 distorted sequences generated by applying five commonly used VFI algorithms to 36 diverse source videos with various spatial resolutions and frame rates.

item.title: GenDexGrasp: Generalizable Dexterous Grasping
item.description: By leveraging the contact map as a hand-agnostic intermediate representation, GenDexGrasp efficiently generates diverse and plausible grasping poses with a high success rate and can transfer among diverse multi-fingered robotic hands.

item.title: Hypothesis Engineering for Zero-Shot Hate Speech Detection
item.description: We find that the zero-shot baseline used for the initial error analysis already outperforms commercial systems and fine-tuned BERT-based hate speech detection models on HateCheck.

item.title: SPARC: Sparse Render-and-Compare for CAD model alignment in a single RGB image
item.description: This combined information is the input to a pose prediction network, SPARC-Net which we train to predict a 9 DoF CAD model pose update.
